THIS-IS-A-PLACEHOLDER-NOT-A-REAL-MUNGE-KEY

This file must be copied from your Slurm controller node, just like the
slurm.conf, accounting.conf, and gres.conf files. It is typically found at
/etc/munge/munge.key on the controller. The key must be identical across all
nodes in the cluster (controller, compute nodes, and login nodes) for MUNGE
authentication to work.

Do not generate a new key here — use the one already deployed on your cluster.
